Summary[edit] Pacific Yew form Description: Pacific Yew (Taxus brevifolia) form. Viewpoint location: French Creek trail 1595. The trail is in the Wenatchee Mountains, an eastern spur of the Cascade Range, located in Wenatchee National Forest, Washington, USA, about 21 km south of Stevens Pass. The trailhead is near the Cle Elum River.
